{"name": "pystaad", "metadata": {"name": "pystaad", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/unrealweb01/pystaad", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pywin32"], "summary": "A Python package to simplify STAAD.Pro automation", "upload_time": 1734366022}, "documentation": ["# Pystaad\r\n\r\nPystaad is a Python package that leverages the OpenSTAAD API to automate STAAD.Pro operations. It enhances the capabilities of STAAD.Pro by adding advanced tools and inbuilt features to streamline structural analysis tasks.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n- **Automates STAAD.Pro operations** using the OpenSTAAD API.\r\n- Includes inbuilt tools for:\r\n  - Generating and applying loads.\r\n  - Modeling tapered sections.\r\n  - Analyzing structures programmatically.\r\n- Simplifies interaction with STAAD.Pro using Python.\r\n- Extends the functionality of OpenSTAAD with advanced features.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\nInstall the package using `pip`:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install pystaad\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pystaad.tools", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pystaad.tools.deg2node", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "degree", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "height", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "distance_from_start_to_mid", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pystaad.tools.maketrussooroof", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pystaad", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pystaad.Root", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pystaad.Geometry", "type": {"name": "GeometryInterface", "xref": {"fqname": "pystaad.GeometryInterface